PRICELESS.Definition: so precious that its value cannot be determined

24/7.Definition: twenty-four hours a day, seven days a week; all the time

CLASSMATES.Definition: someone who is in the same class as you at school

GOAL.Definition: the object of a person's ambition or effort; desired result

STRAIGHT.Definition: continuing in one direction without bending or curving

FIRM.Definition: certain and not likely to change

EXCHANGE.Definition: an act of giving one thing and receiving another in return

REGULAR BASIS.Definition: happening quite often or in a consistent, regular manner

CONSISTENT.Definition: always behaving or happening in a similar way

A BUNCH OF.Definition: a lot of; a number of things

SKILL.Definition: the ability to do something well; expertise

STUCK.Definition: unable to move from a particular position or place

EQUATION.Definition: a mathematical statement consisting of numbers that shows that one amount is equal to another

EQUALS.Definition: the same in amount, number, or size

DOWNSIDE.Definition: a disadvantage of a situation; the negative aspect of something

INTERACT.Definition: to communicate with or react to

ACCENTS.Definition: the way in which people in a particular area, country, or social group pronounce words

DIALECTS.Definition: a form of a language that people speak in a particular part of a country

REALISTIC.Definition: representing familiar things in a way that is accurate or true to life

SERVE.Definition: to help achieve something or to be useful as something

FOR YEARS TO COME.Definition: used to emphasize that something will continue for a long time into the future

AT SOME POINT.Definition: at an indefinite time; sometime; later

COME ACROSS.Definition: meet or find someone or something by chance

EVENTUALLY.Definition: at an unspecified later time; in the end

CURSE THEM OUT.Definition: to say angry and offensive words to (someone)

ACCURATELY.Definition: in a way that is correct in all details; exactly

SUSTAIN.Definition: to cause or allow something to continue for a period of time; to keep alive

MASTER.Definition: to learn how to do it properly or succeed in understanding it completely

WALKS OF LIFE.Definition: various levels of social position or achievement

DIVERSE.Definition: showing a great deal of variety; very different

I JUST CANNOT STRESS ENOUGH.Definition: it is not possible to overemphasize how important something is

MOVE ON.Definition: start doing something new or making progress

HOLD YOU ACCOUNTABLE.Definition: to consider someone responsible for something; to blame something on someone

A WHOLE LOT.Definition: a large amount of; very much

SHOW UP.Definition: to arrive for a gathering or event; to appear

LET OTHER PEOPLE DOWN.Definition: fail to support or help someone as they had hoped or expected

ASSETS.Definition: a useful or valuable thing, person, or quality

SKIP.Definition: to not do something that you usually do; to avoid

FLAKE.Definition: fail to keep an appointment or fulfill a commitment, especially with little or no advance notice

REMINDER.Definition: a thing that causes someone to remember something

SUM.Definition: the total amount resulting from the addition of two or more numbers

DISADVANTAGE.Definition: unfavorable condition that reduces the chances of success or effectiveness

COURT.Definition: a quadrangular area marked out for ball games such as basketball

SHOOTING.Definition: (in soccer, hockey, basketball, etc.) kick, hit, or throw the ball or puck in an attempt to score a goal

DRIBBLING.Definition: (in basketball) moving the ball by repeatedly hitting it so it bounces off the floor

FIELD.Definition: an area, usually covered with grass, used for playing sports

BACK AND FORTH.Definition: to and from; side to side

NET.Definition: a structure consisting of a net supported on a frame, forming the goal in games such as soccer and hockey

MEANT TO BE.Definition: intended to; to be required or supposed

METHODOLOGY.Definition: a system of methods used in a particular area of study or activity

PRACTICAL.Definition: able to provide effective solutions to problems

GROWTH.Definition: an increase in the size or the importance of something

DEVELOP.Definition: to (cause something to) grow or change into a more advanced form

OVER TIME.Definition: it happens gradually during a long period

CLICHE.Definition: a saying that is very often made and is therefore not original and not interesting

TRACK.Definition: to keep track of (something, such as a trend); follow

EVOLUTION.Definition: a gradual process of change and development

WITNESS.Definition: a person who sees an event happening, especially a crime or an accident

STAGES.Definition: a point, period, or step in a process or development

FAR.Definition: at, to, or by a great distance

RECAP.Definition: to repeat the main points of an explanation; recapitulate

ABUNDANCE.Definition: a very large quantity of something

BEYOND.Definition: further away in the distance (than something)

LET OURSELVES SLIDE.Definition: to do nothing about (something, such as another person's mistake or bad behavior)
